 not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":8,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When William Tatton was born in 1329, in Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England, his father, Robert de Tatton, was 33 and his mother, Alice de WITHENSHAW, was 33. He had at least 1 son. He died after 1348."},"et":{"<1329>–AFT 1348/1349":"1329–pärast 1348","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1342–1396":"1342–1396","1297–Male":"1297–Surnud","1297–Female":"1297–Surnud","1337":"1337","1348":"1348","<1329>":"1329","1453":"1453","1342":"1342","1297":"1297","1396":"1396","AFT 1348/1349":"pärast 1348","1329":"1329","<Withenshawe,Chshr,Engl>":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England"},"fi":{"<1329>–AFT 1348/1349":"1329–1348 jälkeen","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1342–1396":"1342–1396","1297–Male":"1297–Kuollut","1297–Female":"1297–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1348":"1348","<1329>":"1329","1453":"1453","1342":"1342","1297":"1297","1396":"1396","AFT 1348/1349":"1348 jälkeen","1329":"1329","<Withenshawe,Chshr,Engl>":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, England"},"fr":{"<1329>–AFT 1348/1349":"1329–après 1348","1329–1348":"1329–1348","1342–1396":"1342–1396","1297–Male":"1297–Décédé","1297–Female":"1297–Décédée","1337":"1337","1348":"1348","<1329>":"1329","1453":"1453","1342":"1342","1297":"1297","1396":"1396","AFT 1348/1349":"après 1348","1329":"1329","<Withenshawe,Chshr,Engl>":"Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque William Tatton est né en 1329, à Wythenshawe, Cheshire, Angleterre, son père, Robert de Tatton, avait 33 ans et sa mère, Alice de WITHENSHAW, avait 33 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décéd